narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Well just make sure you end up taking it with a decent instructor. The learning material itself is quite basic.
Great way to learn how to communicate German at a decent level
Yes, a very good L1/L2 intro course. Doesn't assume any prior knowledge of German (I'm the furthest thing from being German) and I felt like I did fine.
Fun class, easier than Spanish, French, or Chinese, but I still feel like I learned a lot.
Christine Kim is not the most energetic instructor. Shop around. It's not the end of the world if you have to take this section, but there may be better options.
